<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1213,1996]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1357,1383]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[324,346,1357,1383]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">1.</emphasis>
In the original description, 
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, F." box="[667,826,1357,1384]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" pagination="44 - 98" refId="ref9745" refString="Moore, F. (1867) On the Lepidopterous Insects of Bengal. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 53, 44 - 98." type="journal article" year="1867">Moore (1867)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned specimens from two localities (“Calcutta; Darjeeling”) which are 
<typeStatus box="[421,523,1394,1420]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">syntypes</typeStatus>
. In order to stabilize the nomenclature, we hereby designate the male specimen from Darjeeling labelled as ‘Type’ and housed in the NHMUK collection as 
<typeStatus box="[1023,1126,1429,1455]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">lectotype</typeStatus>
and fix the type locality of the species as Darjeeling (north of 
<collectingRegion box="[542,686,1465,1492]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
, north-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[852,914,1465,1492]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">India</collectingCountry>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[933,954,1465,1491]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">2.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[1011,1114,1465,1491]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">lectotype</typeStatus>
male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1867" box="[1213,1337,1465,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albirena">
<emphasis box="[1213,1337,1465,1491]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">L. albirena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was dissected by Tams, who did not mount genitalia on microscope slides and left thousands of badly labeled vials in the collection of NHMUK, which have not been re-curated so far (Alberto Zilli pers. comm.), therefore the genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[226,329,1573,1599]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1867" box="[370,495,1573,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Mamestra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albirena">
<emphasis box="[370,495,1573,1599]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">L. albirena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are currently unavailable for examination. However, the genitalia of the specimen (incorrectly treated as 
<typeStatus box="[406,506,1609,1636]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">holotype</typeStatus>
) were illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Boursin, Ch." box="[742,907,1609,1636]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" pagination="298 - 301" refId="ref8940" refString="Boursin, Ch. (1956) Uber die Gattung Lophotyna Hps. (Lep. Phal. Zenobiinae), Nebst Beschreibung einer neuen Art aus Dr. H. Hones China-Ausbeuten und Angaben uber Hydraecia osseola (= hucherardi Mab.) (Beitrage zur Kenntnis der &quot; Agrotidae- Trifinae &quot;, LXXXVII (87 )). Zeitschrift der Wiener Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 41, 298 - 301. [in German]" type="journal article" year="1956">Boursin (1956</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 31: fig. 6) and they display no remarkable differences from those of the specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[655,722,1645,1671]" name="Nepal" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Nepal</collectingCountry>
dissected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1213,1996]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1681,1707]" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The forewing length is 
<quantity box="[595,717,1681,1708]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="18.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="16.0">16–20 mm</quantity>
in males and 
<quantity box="[877,957,1681,1708]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="18.0">18 mm</quantity>
in females. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[1097,1310,1681,1707]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albirena">
<emphasis box="[1097,1310,1681,1707]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Polymixis albirena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1326,1427,1681,1708]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[184,1403,182,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[173,1413,181,1880]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Polymixis spp.: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 1, 2 and 7 in NHMUK (©The Trustees of NHMUK) (photo by A. Zilli); 3 and 4 in BBT; 5 and 6 in ZFMK (photo by D. Stüning); 8 in HNHM (photo by Zs. Balint &amp; G. Katona)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5089285" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5089285/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
) can easily be distinguished from its congeners by the dark chocolate brown colouration and quite indistinct transverse lines. The male genital capsule structure of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[710,832,1753,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albirena">
<emphasis box="[710,832,1753,1779]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">P. albirena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[848,930,1753,1779]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[171,1411,194,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-34@7.[159,1428,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Polymixis spp.: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 21 in BBT; 22 in ZFMK (photo by D. Stüning); 23 in HNHM (photo by Zs. Balint &amp; G. Katona)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5089293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5089293/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) is reminiscent of that of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[1263,1437,1753,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis box="[1263,1437,1753,1779]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (
<figureCitation box="[322,451,1789,1816]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–26" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,181,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[213,1375,181,1906]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 24–26. Polymixis spp.: male genitalia. The specimens dissected are deposited in BBT." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5089297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5089297/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Figs 24, 25</figureCitation>
) but can easily be distinguished by the symmetrical clavi (they are asymmetrical in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[151,323,1825,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis box="[151,323,1825,1851]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group), the apically rounded dorsal costal protrusion (whereas it is triangular with a pointed tip in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[260,434,1861,1887]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis box="[260,434,1861,1887]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group), the markedly less elongate cucullus, and the relatively larger left digitus which is protruding beyond the ventral margin of the valva (it is conspicuously less elongate in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Owada" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[1264,1437,1897,1923]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="khumbuensis">
<emphasis box="[1264,1437,1897,1923]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">P. khumbuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group). In the female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Babics &amp; Saldaitis" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[626,749,1933,1959]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polymixis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albirena">
<emphasis box="[626,749,1933,1959]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">P. albirena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[766,850,1933,1959]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,185,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[205,1382,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Polymixis spp.: female genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 30, 33–35 in BBT; 31 in ZFMK (photo by D. Stüning); 32 in HNHM (photo by Zs. Balint &amp; G. Katona)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5089303" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5089303/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="28">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
), the ventral ostial margin of the antrum is straight, whereas those of other species-groups are wavy or having a medial ventral protrusion.
</paragraph>
