<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="33" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1149,1248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,523,1149,1176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="33">Distribution and bionomics</emphasis>
. The species is known from north-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[991,1049,1149,1175]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="33">India</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1062,1204,1149,1176]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="11" pageNumber="33">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1256,1339,1149,1176]" country="India" name="Sikkim" pageId="11" pageNumber="33">Sikkim</collectingRegion>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, F." pageId="11" pageNumber="33" pagination="44 - 98" refId="ref9745" refString="Moore, F. (1867) On the Lepidopterous Insects of Bengal. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 53, 44 - 98." type="journal article" year="1867">Moore 1867</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson, G. F." box="[222,393,1186,1212]" pageId="11" pageNumber="33" refId="ref9358" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1910) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum. Vol. 1. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 559 pp." type="book" year="1910">Hampson 1910</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[455,526,1185,1211]" name="Nepal" pageId="11" pageNumber="33">Nepal</collectingCountry>
. The species inhabits monsoon forests at altitudes of 
<quantity box="[1119,1277,1185,1212]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="2150.0" valueMax="2500.0" valueMin="1800.0">1800–2500 m</quantity>
. Adults are on the wing in late autumn (November).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
